<div id="p4" class="ltx_para ltx_noindent">
<p id="p4.1" class="ltx_p">where <math id="p4.1.m1.1" class="ltx_Math" alttext="\rho_{l}" display="inline"><semantics id="p4.1.m1.1a"><msub id="p4.1.m1.1.3" xref="p4.1.m1.1.3.cmml"><mi id="p4.1.m1.1.1" xref="p4.1.m1.1.1.cmml">ρ</mi><mi id="p4.1.m1.1.2.1" xref="p4.1.m1.1.2.1.cmml">l</mi></msub><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content" id="p4.1.m1.1b"><apply id="p4.1.m1.1.3.cmml" xref="p4.1.m1.1.3"><csymbol cd="ambiguous" id="p4.1.m1.1.3.1.cmml" xref="p4.1.m1.1.3">subscript</csymbol><ci id="p4.1.m1.1.1.cmml" xref="p4.1.m1.1.1">𝜌</ci><ci id="p4.1.m1.1.2.1.cmml" xref="p4.1.m1.1.2.1">𝑙</ci></apply></annotation-xml><annotation encoding="application/x-llamapun" id="p4.1.m1.1c">italic-rho POSTSUBSCRIPT:start italic-l POSTSUBSCRIPT:end</annotation><annotation encoding="application/x-tex" id="p4.1.m1.1d">\rho_{l}</annotation></semantics></math> is the number density of the large
particles. As the number <math id="p4.1.m2.1" class="ltx_Math" alttext="n_{b}" display="inline"><semantics id="p4.1.m2.1a"><msub id="p4.1.m2.1.3" xref="p4.1.m2.1.3.cmml"><mi id="p4.1.m2.1.1" xref="p4.1.m2.1.1.cmml">n</mi><mi id="p4.1.m2.1.2.1" xref="p4.1.m2.1.2.1.cmml">b</mi></msub><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content" id="p4.1.m2.1b"><apply id="p4.1.m2.1.3.cmml" xref="p4.1.m2.1.3"><csymbol cd="ambiguous" id="p4.1.m2.1.3.1.cmml" xref="p4.1.m2.1.3">subscript</csymbol><ci id="p4.1.m2.1.1.cmml" xref="p4.1.m2.1.1">𝑛</ci><ci id="p4.1.m2.1.2.1.cmml" xref="p4.1.m2.1.2.1">𝑏</ci></apply></annotation-xml><annotation encoding="application/x-llamapun" id="p4.1.m2.1c">italic-n POSTSUBSCRIPT:start italic-b POSTSUBSCRIPT:end</annotation><annotation encoding="application/x-tex" id="p4.1.m2.1d">n_{b}</annotation></semantics></math> increases with the total
packing fraction, larger and larger aggregates of large
particles appear in the <span id="p4.1.1" class="ltx_text ltx_font_italic">homogeneous</span> fluid phase.
For a sufficiently large number of bonds <math id="p4.1.m3.1" class="ltx_Math" alttext="n_{c}" display="inline"><semantics id="p4.1.m3.1a"><msub id="p4.1.m3.1.3" xref="p4.1.m3.1.3.cmml"><mi id="p4.1.m3.1.1" xref="p4.1.m3.1.1.cmml">n</mi><mi id="p4.1.m3.1.2.1" xref="p4.1.m3.1.2.1.cmml">c</mi></msub><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content" id="p4.1.m3.1b"><apply id="p4.1.m3.1.3.cmml" xref="p4.1.m3.1.3"><csymbol cd="ambiguous" id="p4.1.m3.1.3.1.cmml" xref="p4.1.m3.1.3">subscript</csymbol><ci id="p4.1.m3.1.1.cmml" xref="p4.1.m3.1.1">𝑛</ci><ci id="p4.1.m3.1.2.1.cmml" xref="p4.1.m3.1.2.1">𝑐</ci></apply></annotation-xml><annotation encoding="application/x-llamapun" id="p4.1.m3.1c">italic-n POSTSUBSCRIPT:start italic-c POSTSUBSCRIPT:end</annotation><annotation encoding="application/x-tex" id="p4.1.m3.1d">n_{c}</annotation></semantics></math> or
equivalently a sufficiently large packing fraction,
a macroscopic aggregate appears in the system.
This macroscopic aggregate breaks the translational
invariance of the system which is no more homogeneous.
Thus, the homogeneous fluid phase is instable.
In the letter <cite class="ltx_cite ltx_citemacro_cite">[<a href="#bib.bib1" title="" class="ltx_ref">1</a>]</cite> I approximate the number
<math id="p4.1.m4.1" class="ltx_Math" alttext="n_{c}" display="inline"><semantics id="p4.1.m4.1a"><msub id="p4.1.m4.1.3" xref="p4.1.m4.1.3.cmml"><mi id="p4.1.m4.1.1" xref="p4.1.m4.1.1.cmml">n</mi><mi id="p4.1.m4.1.2.1" xref="p4.1.m4.1.2.1.cmml">c</mi></msub><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content" id="p4.1.m4.1b"><apply id="p4.1.m4.1.3.cmml" xref="p4.1.m4.1.3"><csymbol cd="ambiguous" id="p4.1.m4.1.3.1.cmml" xref="p4.1.m4.1.3">subscript</csymbol><ci id="p4.1.m4.1.1.cmml" xref="p4.1.m4.1.1">𝑛</ci><ci id="p4.1.m4.1.2.1.cmml" xref="p4.1.m4.1.2.1">𝑐</ci></apply></annotation-xml><annotation encoding="application/x-llamapun" id="p4.1.m4.1c">italic-n POSTSUBSCRIPT:start italic-c POSTSUBSCRIPT:end</annotation><annotation encoding="application/x-tex" id="p4.1.m4.1d">n_{c}</annotation></semantics></math> by the number of bonds <math id="p4.1.m5.1" class="ltx_Math" alttext="zp_{c}" display="inline"><semantics id="p4.1.m5.1a"><mrow id="p4.1.m5.1.4" xref="p4.1.m5.1.4.cmml"><mi id="p4.1.m5.1.1" xref="p4.1.m5.1.1.cmml">z</mi><mo id="p4.1.m5.1.4.1" xref="p4.1.m5.1.4.1.cmml">⁢</mo><msub id="p4.1.m5.1.4.2" xref="p4.1.m5.1.4.2.cmml"><mi id="p4.1.m5.1.2" xref="p4.1.m5.1.2.cmml">p</mi><mi id="p4.1.m5.1.3.1" xref="p4.1.m5.1.3.1.cmml">c</mi></msub></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content" id="p4.1.m5.1b"><apply id="p4.1.m5.1.4.cmml" xref="p4.1.m5.1.4"><times id="p4.1.m5.1.4.1.cmml" xref="p4.1.m5.1.4.1"></times><ci id="p4.1.m5.1.1.cmml" xref="p4.1.m5.1.1">𝑧</ci><apply id="p4.1.m5.1.4.2.cmml" xref="p4.1.m5.1.4.2"><csymbol cd="ambiguous" id="p4.1.m5.1.4.2.1.cmml" xref="p4.1.m5.1.4.2">subscript</csymbol><ci id="p4.1.m5.1.2.cmml" xref="p4.1.m5.1.2">𝑝</ci><ci id="p4.1.m5.1.3.1.cmml" xref="p4.1.m5.1.3.1">𝑐</ci></apply></apply></annotation-xml><annotation encoding="application/x-llamapun" id="p4.1.m5.1c">italic-z italic-p POSTSUBSCRIPT:start italic-c POSTSUBSCRIPT:end</annotation><annotation encoding="application/x-tex" id="p4.1.m5.1d">zp_{c}</annotation></semantics></math> at the bond-percolation
transition of the corresponding crystal lattice of large
particles where <math id="p4.1.m6.1" class="ltx_Math" alttext="z" display="inline"><semantics id="p4.1.m6.1a"><mi id="p4.1.m6.1.1" xref="p4.1.m6.1.1.cmml">z</mi><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content" id="p4.1.m6.1b"><ci id="p4.1.m6.1.1.cmml" xref="p4.1.m6.1.1">𝑧</ci></annotation-xml><annotation encoding="application/x-llamapun" id="p4.1.m6.1c">italic-z</annotation><annotation encoding="application/x-tex" id="p4.1.m6.1d">z</annotation></semantics></math> is the coordination number and <math id="p4.1.m7.1" class="ltx_Math" alttext="p_{c}" display="inline"><semantics id="p4.1.m7.1a"><msub id="p4.1.m7.1.3" xref="p4.1.m7.1.3.cmml"><mi id="p4.1.m7.1.1" xref="p4.1.m7.1.1.cmml">p</mi><mi id="p4.1.m7.1.2.1" xref="p4.1.m7.1.2.1.cmml">c</mi></msub><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content" id="p4.1.m7.1b"><apply id="p4.1.m7.1.3.cmml" xref="p4.1.m7.1.3"><csymbol cd="ambiguous" id="p4.1.m7.1.3.1.cmml" xref="p4.1.m7.1.3">subscript</csymbol><ci id="p4.1.m7.1.1.cmml" xref="p4.1.m7.1.1">𝑝</ci><ci id="p4.1.m7.1.2.1.cmml" xref="p4.1.m7.1.2.1">𝑐</ci></apply></annotation-xml><annotation encoding="application/x-llamapun" id="p4.1.m7.1c">italic-p POSTSUBSCRIPT:start italic-c POSTSUBSCRIPT:end</annotation><annotation encoding="application/x-tex" id="p4.1.m7.1d">p_{c}</annotation></semantics></math>
the bond-percolation threshold. This approximation
neglects two effects : the slight modification due to the
lack of lattice and, more important, the possible
correlations between bonds.
Taking into account those possible correlations,
the appearance of the solid phase (or macroscopic aggregate)
will be shift to a lower number of bonds (<math id="p4.1.m8.1" class="ltx_Math" alttext="n_{c}&lt;zp_{c}" display="inline"><semantics id="p4.1.m8.1a"><mrow id="p4.1.m8.1.7" xref="p4.1.m8.1.7.cmml"><msub id="p4.1.m8.1.7.1" xref="p4.1.m8.1.7.1.cmml"><mi id="p4.1.m8.1.1" xref="p4.1.m8.1.1.cmml">n</mi><mi id="p4.1.m8.1.2.1" xref="p4.1.m8.1.2.1.cmml">c</mi></msub><mo id="p4.1.m8.1.3" xref="p4.1.m8.1.3.cmml">&lt;</mo><mrow id="p4.1.m8.1.7.2" xref="p4.1.m8.1.7.2.cmml"><mi id="p4.1.m8.1.4" xref="p4.1.m8.1.4.cmml">z</mi><mo id="p4.1.m8.1.7.2.1" xref="p4.1.m8.1.7.2.1.cmml">⁢</mo><msub id="p4.1.m8.1.7.2.2" xref="p4.1.m8.1.7.2.2.cmml"><mi id="p4.1.m8.1.5" xref="p4.1.m8.1.5.cmml">p</mi><mi id="p4.1.m8.1.6.1" xref="p4.1.m8.1.6.1.cmml">c</mi></msub></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content" id="p4.1.m8.1b"><apply id="p4.1.m8.1.7.cmml" xref="p4.1.m8.1.7"><lt id="p4.1.m8.1.3.cmml" xref="p4.1.m8.1.3"></lt><apply id="p4.1.m8.1.7.1.cmml" xref="p4.1.m8.1.7.1"><csymbol cd="ambiguous" id="p4.1.m8.1.7.1.1.cmml" xref="p4.1.m8.1.7.1">subscript</csymbol><ci id="p4.1.m8.1.1.cmml" xref="p4.1.m8.1.1">𝑛</ci><ci id="p4.1.m8.1.2.1.cmml" xref="p4.1.m8.1.2.1">𝑐</ci></apply><apply id="p4.1.m8.1.7.2.cmml" xref="p4.1.m8.1.7.2"><times id="p4.1.m8.1.7.2.1.cmml" xref="p4.1.m8.1.7.2.1"></times><ci id="p4.1.m8.1.4.cmml" xref="p4.1.m8.1.4">𝑧</ci><apply id="p4.1.m8.1.7.2.2.cmml" xref="p4.1.m8.1.7.2.2"><csymbol cd="ambiguous" id="p4.1.m8.1.7.2.2.1.cmml" xref="p4.1.m8.1.7.2.2">subscript</csymbol><ci id="p4.1.m8.1.5.cmml" xref="p4.1.m8.1.5">𝑝</ci><ci id="p4.1.m8.1.6.1.cmml" xref="p4.1.m8.1.6.1">𝑐</ci></apply></apply></apply></annotation-xml><annotation encoding="application/x-llamapun" id="p4.1.m8.1c">italic-n POSTSUBSCRIPT:start italic-c POSTSUBSCRIPT:end RELOP:less-than italic-z italic-p POSTSUBSCRIPT:start italic-c POSTSUBSCRIPT:end</annotation><annotation encoding="application/x-tex" id="p4.1.m8.1d">n_{c}&lt;zp_{c}</annotation></semantics></math>).
The packing fraction <math id="p4.1.m9.1" class="ltx_Math" alttext="\eta_{c}" display="inline"><semantics id="p4.1.m9.1a"><msub id="p4.1.m9.1.3" xref="p4.1.m9.1.3.cmml"><mi id="p4.1.m9.1.1" xref="p4.1.m9.1.1.cmml">η</mi><mi id="p4.1.m9.1.2.1" xref="p4.1.m9.1.2.1.cmml">c</mi></msub><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content" id="p4.1.m9.1b"><apply id="p4.1.m9.1.3.cmml" xref="p4.1.m9.1.3"><csymbol cd="ambiguous" id="p4.1.m9.1.3.1.cmml" xref="p4.1.m9.1.3">subscript</csymbol><ci id="p4.1.m9.1.1.cmml" xref="p4.1.m9.1.1">𝜂</ci><ci id="p4.1.m9.1.2.1.cmml" xref="p4.1.m9.1.2.1">𝑐</ci></apply></annotation-xml><annotation encoding="application/x-llamapun" id="p4.1.m9.1c">italic-eta POSTSUBSCRIPT:start italic-c POSTSUBSCRIPT:end</annotation><annotation encoding="application/x-tex" id="p4.1.m9.1d">\eta_{c}</annotation></semantics></math> corresponding to <math id="p4.1.m10.1" class="ltx_Math" alttext="n_{b}=zp_{c}" display="inline"><semantics id="p4.1.m10.1a"><mrow id="p4.1.m10.1.7" xref="p4.1.m10.1.7.cmml"><msub id="p4.1.m10.1.7.1" xref="p4.1.m10.1.7.1.cmml"><mi id="p4.1.m10.1.1" xref="p4.1.m10.1.1.cmml">n</mi><mi id="p4.1.m10.1.2.1" xref="p4.1.m10.1.2.1.cmml">b</mi></msub><mo id="p4.1.m10.1.3" xref="p4.1.m10.1.3.cmml">=</mo><mrow id="p4.1.m10.1.7.2" xref="p4.1.m10.1.7.2.cmml"><mi id="p4.1.m10.1.4" xref="p4.1.m10.1.4.cmml">z</mi><mo id="p4.1.m10.1.7.2.1" xref="p4.1.m10.1.7.2.1.cmml">⁢</mo><msub id="p4.1.m10.1.7.2.2" xref="p4.1.m10.1.7.2.2.cmml"><mi id="p4.1.m10.1.5" xref="p4.1.m10.1.5.cmml">p</mi><mi id="p4.1.m10.1.6.1" xref="p4.1.m10.1.6.1.cmml">c</mi></msub></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content" id="p4.1.m10.1b"><apply id="p4.1.m10.1.7.cmml" xref="p4.1.m10.1.7"><eq id="p4.1.m10.1.3.cmml" xref="p4.1.m10.1.3"></eq><apply id="p4.1.m10.1.7.1.cmml" xref="p4.1.m10.1.7.1"><csymbol cd="ambiguous" id="p4.1.m10.1.7.1.1.cmml" xref="p4.1.m10.1.7.1">subscript</csymbol><ci id="p4.1.m10.1.1.cmml" xref="p4.1.m10.1.1">𝑛</ci><ci id="p4.1.m10.1.2.1.cmml" xref="p4.1.m10.1.2.1">𝑏</ci></apply><apply id="p4.1.m10.1.7.2.cmml" xref="p4.1.m10.1.7.2"><times id="p4.1.m10.1.7.2.1.cmml" xref="p4.1.m10.1.7.2.1"></times><ci id="p4.1.m10.1.4.cmml" xref="p4.1.m10.1.4">𝑧</ci><apply id="p4.1.m10.1.7.2.2.cmml" xref="p4.1.m10.1.7.2.2"><csymbol cd="ambiguous" id="p4.1.m10.1.7.2.2.1.cmml" xref="p4.1.m10.1.7.2.2">subscript</csymbol><ci id="p4.1.m10.1.5.cmml" xref="p4.1.m10.1.5">𝑝</ci><ci id="p4.1.m10.1.6.1.cmml" xref="p4.1.m10.1.6.1">𝑐</ci></apply></apply></apply></annotation-xml><annotation encoding="application/x-llamapun" id="p4.1.m10.1c">italic-n POSTSUBSCRIPT:start italic-b POSTSUBSCRIPT:end RELOP:equals italic-z italic-p POSTSUBSCRIPT:start italic-c POSTSUBSCRIPT:end</annotation><annotation encoding="application/x-tex" id="p4.1.m10.1d">n_{b}=zp_{c}</annotation></semantics></math>
is thus only an upper bond of the packing fraction <math id="p4.1.m11.1" class="ltx_Math" alttext="\eta_{t}" display="inline"><semantics id="p4.1.m11.1a"><msub id="p4.1.m11.1.3" xref="p4.1.m11.1.3.cmml"><mi id="p4.1.m11.1.1" xref="p4.1.m11.1.1.cmml">η</mi><mi id="p4.1.m11.1.2.1" xref="p4.1.m11.1.2.1.cmml">t</mi></msub><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content" id="p4.1.m11.1b"><apply id="p4.1.m11.1.3.cmml" xref="p4.1.m11.1.3"><csymbol cd="ambiguous" id="p4.1.m11.1.3.1.cmml" xref="p4.1.m11.1.3">subscript</csymbol><ci id="p4.1.m11.1.1.cmml" xref="p4.1.m11.1.1">𝜂</ci><ci id="p4.1.m11.1.2.1.cmml" xref="p4.1.m11.1.2.1">𝑡</ci></apply></annotation-xml><annotation encoding="application/x-llamapun" id="p4.1.m11.1c">italic-eta POSTSUBSCRIPT:start italic-t POSTSUBSCRIPT:end</annotation><annotation encoding="application/x-tex" id="p4.1.m11.1d">\eta_{t}</annotation></semantics></math>
at the phase-separation transition between the fluid phase
and the fluid-solid phase.</p>
